messages.content: What are the ComfyUI nodes for ControlNeXt-SVD v2?
The ComfyUI nodes for ControlNeXt-SVD v2 include a wrapper for the original diffusers pipeline and a work in progress native ComfyUI implementation.
How can the unet be obtained for the native ComfyUI implementation of ControlNeXt-SVD v2?

The unet for the native ComfyUI implementation of ControlNeXt-SVD v2 can be obtained from https://huggingface.co/Kijai/ControlNeXt-SVD-V2-Comfy/blob/main/controlnext-svd_v2-unet-fp16_converted.safetensors.
Where can the diffusers wrapper for ControlNeXt-SVD v2 in ComfyUI be found?
The diffusers wrapper for ControlNeXt-SVD v2 in ComfyUI can be found at https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/9bc06d4c-b29a-45f5-8a67-211dd5d0f555.
Where can the native ComfyUI implementation for ControlNeXt-SVD v2 be found?
The native ComfyUI implementation for ControlNeXt-SVD v2 can be found at https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7ed23e44-3652-4ccb-8a48-5f0c703ed8b9.
Where can the original repository for ControlNeXt-SVD v2 be found?
The original repository for ControlNeXt-SVD v2 can be found at https://github.com/dvlab-research/ControlNeXt/tree/main/ControlNeXt-SVD-v2.
Are the models for the diffusers wrapper in ComfyUI nodes for ControlNeXt-SVD v2 downloaded automatically?
Yes, the models for the diffusers wrapper in ComfyUI nodes for ControlNeXt-SVD v2 are downloaded automatically.
Is the native ComfyUI implementation for ControlNeXt-SVD v2 a finished product?
No, the native ComfyUI implementation for ControlNeXt-SVD v2 is a work in progress and not a finished product.
